hopobject.body: Could you give me some smaller notes? ibuprofen 800 get high Kevin Croft, president of the Healthcare People Management Association, comments: “These survey results are disappointing but similar to messages from the national staff survey.Â  The findings reinforce the need for a much greater focus on the staff experience, good people management and staff engagement, at both a system and local level, to improve the patient experience. We know there is a clear correlation between a positive staff experience and better health outcomes for patients. Good quality people management information which shines a light on these issues can play a crucial role in helping care providers understand what underpins good patient care and provide earlier insight if things are going wrong.”
